    // If we consider the weights modulo 2 (i.e., 0 or 1), the condition is that the cycle basis must have XOR sum 0.
    // This is equivalent to maintaining connected components where the distance parity (or potential) between any two nodes in the same component is fixed.

    // We can use a Disjoint Set Union (DSU) structure, augmented to track the parity of the path from a node to the representative of its set.
    // Let dist[i] be the parity of the path weight from node i to its current parent in the DSU tree.

    const parent = Array(n).fill(0).map((_, i) => i);
    // parity[i] stores the XOR sum of edge weights on the path from i to parent[i].
    const parity = Array(n).fill(0); 

